<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="235" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">790g.00/l</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Baghdad</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Randolph</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-06">May 6, 1929</date>.<lb/>[Received May
                                28.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 875</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>The treaty between the United States, Great Britain and Iraq, which has
                            been under negotiation during the last three years, was about to be
                            signed by the Iraq Government just before the resignation of the late
                            Cabinet of Sir Abdul Muhsin Beg al Sa’dun, its provisions being
                            agreeable at that time to the Iraq Government. From statements made to
                            me by the new Prime Minister, during a recent informal conversation, I
                            understand that the provisions in the draft regarding the Capitulations
                            are probably no longer agreeable to the Iraq Government.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Randolph</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>